The compiler should actually refuse to compile. When resolving `this`, the only instance available is the anonymous runnable you created using `new Runnable()`, which is not derived from Main.

On top of that Java runs the `public static void main(...)` method without creating any instance of `Main`, so you have nothing that you can refer to.

Therefore, change the one line into something like

    this.myJFrame = new MyJFrame(new Main());

and it should compile. Whether that does what you need is still up to you.

